      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LA SIGNORA DANE (5) resumed four weeks ago over 1103m at Roebourne and was only beaten 1.5 lengths into fourth. Second up record is very strong. Fitter this time. Hard to beat in this suitable race. CALATHINITE (6) was sent forward last time out and boxed on to finish a head from the winner in second at this track over 1200m. Strong record with Elisha Whittington in the irons, including a win. Will strip fitter so expect him to feature. STAR POWER (2) finished fourth two runs back then improved last start but found a couple better over 1103m at Roebourne, beaten 2.75 lengths. Kyra Yuill gets the best out of this six-year-old mare. Well placed and there is no reason she cannot find winning ways. LEADING TADDY (3) settled well back and turned in a mediocre run last time out over 1200m at this track after a nice win the start prior. Nicely placed to bounce back. CASSENITE (7) is racing well and can give a bit of cheek again.",
